<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 19 at 2:37PM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Brief Heavy Snow Showers Across Chicagoland and Northwest
Indiana...
Through 330 PM, snow showers will continue to stream across the
Chicago metro and northwest Indiana. Within the broader area of
snow showers, brief but intense bursts of snow will continue to
cause sharply reduced visibility and a quick dusting of snow.
Motorists are advised to use extra caution when driving this
afternoon. Expect to encounter rapidly changing conditions in and
near the heaviest snow showers. Slow down and increase following
distance when driving in heavy snow.</description>
